<TITLE> US envoy to India in town to talk anti-terror steps </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 21 (bdnews24.com)The US ambassador to India Timothy J Roemer is in Dhaka to discuss the India-Bangladesh relations and ways to strengthen counter terrorism programmes, officials say. Roemer flew in on Wednesday afternoon ahead of the visit of the US deputy secretary of state James B Steinberg who is now touring South Asia. Steinberg, who went to India on April 10, is due Thursday, the embassy officials say. Government officials say Roemer will see prime minister Sheikh Hasina at her residence on Thursday evening. US ambassador James F Moriarty will accompany him, according to the officials. "Ambassador Roemer's meetings in Dhaka will focus on the growing prospects between Bangladesh and India for improved counterterrorism cooperation, trade and development, and regional integration," a spokesman for the American Centre told bdnews24.com on Wednesday. The embassy officials say Steinberg will also call on prime minister Sheikh Hasina, leader of the opposition Khaleda Zia and foreign minister Dipu Moni on Thursday
